Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and specifically part-of-speech tagging. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper uses hierarchical Bayesian models and Markov Chain Monte Carlo sampling techniques for inference. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with unsupervised learning and multilingual learning, which are both relevant to AI. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is less likely but still possible as the paper may use neural network models for part-of-speech tagging. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is unlikely as the paper does not focus on data structures or algorithms, but rather on machine learning and natural language processing.
